                  >
                </li>
                <li>
                  <i class="fas fa-tags"></i>
                  <a href="#">Catalyzing Capital for Social Good</a>
                </li>
                <!-- <li><i class="flaticon-speech-bubble"></i><a href="#">05 Comments</a></li> -->
              </ul>
            </div>

            <p>
              In a world shaped by widening inequalities, climate disruption and
              systemic fragility, the very notion of finance is being
              reimagined. The question is no longer how much capital we can
              generate, but what kind of impact that capital creates. <br />
              <br /> At DR Associates, we believe the answer lies in a powerful convergence:
              Impact Investing through the Social Stock Exchange (SSE) - a visionary
              platform launched by the National Stock Exchange of India (NSE) and
              also on Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) under SEBI’s regulatory framework.
            </p>
            <b><p>The Rise of Purpose-Driven Capital</p></b>
            <!-- <ul>
              <li>
                Access to verified NGOs aligned with national & global
                development goals
              </li>
              <li>SEBI-compliant impact tracking and reporting</li>
            </ul> -->
            <p>
              Traditional investing has long prioritized profit above all else.
              Philanthropy, on the other hand, has sought to address social
              issues but often with limited scale, speed, or accountability.
              Impact investing bridges this gap - deploying capital not only for
              financial returns but also to generate measurable, positive social
              and environmental outcomes. <br />
              <br />
              The Social Stock Exchange, introduced in India in 2023, institutionalizes
              this dual-purpose approach. It allows eligible non-profits and social
              enterprises to raise funds from institutional and retail investors
              via innovative instruments like Zero Coupon Zero Principal (ZCZP) bonds
              - designed to unlock capital for social transformation. <br />

              This is not a trend — it’s a tectonic shift.
            </p>

            <!-- <blockquote>
